{"id":14881016,"mediaExerciseId":"35e767f6-c319-413c-b6bb-ec197607018c","exerciseName":"78","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612301,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":192,"solutions":[{"id":6353956,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will derive a formula for the present value of a growing annuity given that the payments and rate are variables.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The present value for growing annuity refers to the present value of future payments in a given time as the payments grow at a particular rate. The formula for this is given as:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{PV for growing annuity}&=\\dfrac{\\text{Cashflow}}{\\text{return rate}-\\text{growth rate}} \\times \\left(1-\\left[\\dfrac{1+\\text{growth rate}}{1+\\text{return rate}}\\right]^\\text{time}\\right)\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"In the given problem, the cash flow and growth rate are represented as $\\text{C}$, therefore, substituting this to the formula, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{PV for growing annuity}&=\\dfrac{\\text{C}}{\\text{return rate}-\\text{C}} \\times \\left(1-\\left[\\dfrac{1+\\text{C}}{1+\\text{return rate}}\\right]^\\text{time}\\right)\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"f1bf9afa-d5f3-48ee-9d76-bc10098cf93d","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881017,"exerciseName":"79","page":192,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6312498a-e000-4114-9e6e-b6bc32c8b70e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-79-6312498a-e000-4114-9e6e-b6bc32c8b70e"},{"id":14881018,"exerciseName":"80","page":192,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"e29b91f8-d6d0-445f-86be-197f2b042cf1","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-80-e29b91f8-d6d0-445f-86be-197f2b042cf1"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881015,"exerciseName":"77","page":192,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"711ce4fe-ceed-4d24-97ea-d7513fd8726d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-77-711ce4fe-ceed-4d24-97ea-d7513fd8726d"},{"id":14881014,"exerciseName":"76","page":192,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d6954f6d-5a68-41eb-bc58-728fd5e55bb0","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-76-d6954f6d-5a68-41eb-bc58-728fd5e55bb0"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-78-35e767f6-c